instruction:
Write a function `addProperty` that takes three parameters:
* `obj` - object
* `key` - key
* `value` - value

The function must add a new property with key `key` and value `value` to the object.

The function must return the updated object.

An example of running the function:
```javascript
addProperty({ name: "Mike" }, "age", 45); // { name: "Mike", age: 45 }
addProperty({ car: "BMW" }, "year", 2020); // { car: "BMW", year: 2020 }
```

Similar example:
```javascript
function addField(car, fieldKey, fieldValue) {
car[fieldKey] = fieldValue;
return car;
}

console.log(addField({ car: "BMW" }, "year", 2020)); // { car: "BMW", year: 2020 }
```
